Parse PubMed XML file
#install.packages("data.table")
#install.packages("tidyverse")
library(XML)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(data.table)
library(tidyverse)


path <- "/Users/soumengchea/Desktop/"
fn <- "pubmed_sample.xml"
fpn = paste0(path, fn)

# Reading the XML file and parse into DOM
xml_data <- xmlParse(file = fpn)
nodes <- getNodeSet(xml_data, "//PubmedArticle")

xmlRoot <- xmlRoot(xml_data)

# Get the name of the node
xmlName(xmlRoot)
[1] "PubmedArticleSet"
# Get the number of nodes in root
xmlSize(xmlRoot)
[1] 19
Get author last name, first name, initials and affilication
# get pmid
pmid <- xpathSApply(xml_data,"//MedlineCitation/PMID", xmlValue)

# get author last names 
last_name <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//Author/LastName", xmlValue)
last_name[sapply(last_name, is.list)] <- NA

# get author first names
first_name <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//Author/ForeName", xmlValue)
first_name[sapply(first_name, is.list)] <- NA

# get author initials
init <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//Author/Initials", xmlValue)
init[sapply(init, is.list)] <- NA

#   combine authors together
authors <- mapply(paste, last_name, first_name, init, collapse = ",")
authors <- as.character(authors)

# get affiliations for all authors, apply NA for authors without affiliation
affiliation<-xpathSApply(xml_data, "//Author", function(x) {
  author_affiliation <- xmlValue(x[["Affiliation"]])})
affiliation[sapply(affiliation, is.list)] <- NA
    
# write authors to dataframe, then separate authors (to associate with correct pmid)
df_author <- data.frame(pmid, authors, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
df_author <- df_author  %>% mutate(authors = strsplit(authors, ",")) %>% unnest(authors)

# add affiliation to dataframe and replace NAs with empty strings
df_author$affiliation <- affiliation
nas <- which(is.na(df_author[,3]))
df_author[nas,3] <- " "


# split author name to last name, first name, initial
df_author <- df_author %>% separate(authors, c("name", "init"), sep="\\s+(?=\\S*$)")
df_author <- df_author %>% separate(name, c("last_name", "first_name"), sep="\\s", extra = "merge")

Get article doi, pub model, abstract, title
# get pmid
pmid <- xpathSApply(xml_data, "//MedlineCitation/PMID", xmlValue)

pubmodel <- xpathSApply(xml_data, "//MedlineCitation/Article", xmlAttrs)

doi <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//ELocationID[@EIdType = \"doi\"]", xmlValue)
doi[sapply(doi, is.list)] <- NA
doi <- unlist(doi)

abstract <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//Abstract/AbstractText", xmlValue)
abstract[sapply(abstract, is.list)] <- NA
abstract <- sapply(abstract, paste, collapse = "|")

title <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//ArticleTitle", xmlValue) 
title[sapply(title, is.list)] <- NA
title <- unlist(title)


df_article <- data.frame(pmid, doi, pubmodel, abstract, title, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
Get the dates created, completed, revised
# get date created
year_created <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//MedlineCitation/DateCreated/Year", xmlValue)
year_created[sapply(year_created, is.list)] <- NA
month_created <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//MedlineCitation/DateCreated/Month", xmlValue)
month_created[sapply(month_created, is.list)] <- NA
day_created <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//MedlineCitation/DateCreated/Day", xmlValue)
day_created[sapply(day_created, is.list)] <- NA
created <- mapply(paste, year_created, month_created, day_created, collapse = "")
created[created == ""]<- NA

# get date completed
year_completed <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//MedlineCitation/DateCompleted/Year", xmlValue)
year_completed[sapply(year_completed, is.list)] <- NA
month_completed <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//MedlineCitation/DateCompleted//Month", xmlValue)
month_completed[sapply(as.numeric(month_completed), is.list)] <- NA
day_completed <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//MedlineCitation/DateCompleted/Day", xmlValue)
day_completed[sapply(day_completed, is.list)] <- NA
completed <- mapply(paste, year_completed, month_completed, day_completed, collapse = "")
completed[completed == ""]<- NA

# get date revised
year_revised <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//MedlineCitation/DateCompleted/Year", xmlValue)
year_revised[sapply(year_revised, is.list)] <- NA
month_revised <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//MedlineCitation/DateCompleted//Month", xmlValue)
month_revised[sapply(month_revised, is.list)] <- NA
day_revised <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//MedlineCitation/DateCompleted/Day", xmlValue)
day_revised[sapply(day_revised, is.list)] <- NA
revised <- mapply(paste, year_revised, month_revised, day_revised, collapse = "")
revised[revised == ""]<- NA

# format date created
df_article$date_created <- created
df_article$date_created <- sub(" ", "-", df_article$date_created)
df_article$date_created <- sub(" ", "-", df_article$date_created)

# format date completed
df_article$date_completed <- completed
df_article$date_completed <- sub(" ", "-", df_article$date_completed)
df_article$date_completed <- sub(" ", "-", df_article$date_completed)

# format date revised
df_article$date_revised <- revised
df_article$date_revised <- sub(" ", "-", df_article$date_revised)
df_article$date_revised <- sub(" ", "-", df_article$date_revised)

# add pub year and pub month
pub_year <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//Journal/JournalIssue/PubDate/Year", xmlValue)
pub_year[sapply(pub_year, is.list)] <- NA
pub_year <- unlist(pub_year)
df_article$pub_year <- pub_year
nas <- which(is.na(df_article[,9]))
df_article[nas,9] <- " "

pub_month <- lapply(nodes, xpathSApply, ".//Journal/JournalIssue/PubDate/Month", xmlValue)
pub_month[sapply(pub_month, is.list)] <- NA
pub_month <- unlist(pub_month)
df_article$pub_month <- pub_month
nas <- which(is.na(df_article[,10]))
df_article[nas,10] <- " "

Part 3

Part 3.1

Find number of publications per season

pubs_per_season = dbSendQuery(pub, "SELECT COUNT(pmID) as 'Publications', season FROM star.article_fact GROUP BY season;")
df_pubs_per_season<-dbFetch(pubs_per_season)

Find total time spent (in days) on articles grouped by the season they were published

time_per_season = dbSendStatement(pub, "SELECT SUM(timeToComplete) as 'Days', season FROM star.article_fact GROUP BY season;")
df_time_per_season<-dbFetch(time_per_season)

Find number of authors publishing per season

author_per_season = dbSendStatement(pub, "SELECT SUM(numAuthors) as 'Authors', season FROM star.article_fact GROUP BY season;")
df_author_per_season<-dbFetch(author_per_season)

Find number of publications per season by author Mazumdar

mazumdar = dbSendQuery(pub, "SELECT COUNT(star.articles.pmID) as 'Publications', season 
                              FROM star.article_fact
                              JOIN star.articles on star.articles.pmID = star.article_fact.pmID
                              JOIN star.author on star.articles.authorID = star.author.authorID
                              WHERE star.author.lastName LIKE 'Mazumdar'
                              GROUP BY season;")
df_mazumdar<-dbFetch(mazumdar)

Find number days spent on publication per season by author Chiu

chiu = dbSendQuery(pub, "SELECT SUM(timeToComplete) as 'Days', season 
                              FROM star.article_fact
                              JOIN star.articles on star.articles.pmID = star.article_fact.pmID
                              JOIN star.author on star.articles.authorID = star.author.authorID
                              WHERE star.author.lastName LIKE 'Chiu'
                              GROUP BY season;")
df_chiu<-dbFetch(chiu)

Explanation

Querying the article fact table, we are able to more easily find the number of articles published per season, the total time spent on the articles by the season they were first published, and the number of authors publishing articles per season. Additional queries in the star schema could also allow us to find one author’s number of publications per season. For example, we chose to search for the number of publications the author with the last name Mazumdar published per season. We then used a similar query to find the amount of time that author with the last name Chiu spent publishing by season.
